+{"id":"bd-2ww","title":"Add consistent detail-pane navigation across all TUI view modes","description":"History mode supports J/K detail navigation for related beads, but board, graph, and insights detail panes lack similar navigation shortcuts. Add Tab focus toggle and j/k/J/K navigation for blocker/dependent lists in board detail, graph detail, and insights detail panes.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-02-27T19:03:07.669344140Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T19:46:22.563909178Z","closed_at":"2026-02-27T19:46:22.563890923Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"bd-33w","title":"Parity Closure Program: bvr must fully match legacy bv (robot + TUI + integrations)","description":"Background: bvr currently has meaningful progress but still trails the legacy Go beads_viewer in command surface, integration features, and TUI fidelity.\\nGoal: deliver true feature/functionality parity with explicit proof, not aspirational parity.\\nScope: robot CLI contracts, interactive TUI behavior/appearance, workspace/hooks/export ecosystem, performance and reliability under scale.\\nAcceptance: every legacy surface has a mapped bvr equivalent (or explicit intentional exclusion), parity report reaches complete, and conformance/e2e evidence is green.\\nTesting & logging requirement: all child work must include deterministic tests and verbose diagnostics useful for failure triage in CI and local runs.","status":"blocked","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:52.918444947Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T22:26:28.384552358Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["parity","porting","program"]}
+{"id":"bd-33w.1","title":"Spec-First Parity Contract and Gap Ledger","description":"Background: porting-to-rust guidance requires spec extraction first, implementation second.\\nGoal: create a single authoritative contract for what 'full parity' means.\\nDeliverables: command-by-command behavior contract, field-level output contract, and visual/keybinding TUI contract.\\nAcceptance: implementation teams can work without re-reading legacy ad hoc; all downstream epics reference this contract.","status":"blocked","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:55.093818544Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T22:26:28.474800713Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["parity","planning","spec"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-33w.1","depends_on_id":"bd-33w","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-05T00:07:49Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-33w.1.1","title":"Build authoritative legacy->bvr command/flag parity ledger","description":"Background: the current gap includes many legacy flags absent in bvr.\\nWork: enumerate every legacy CLI/robot flag, classify status (implemented/partial/missing/excluded), and document exact behavior contracts including defaults and error modes.\\nAcceptance: FEATURE_PARITY.md contains a machine-checkable ledger mapping legacy flags to bvr implementation tasks and tests; no unclassified surfaces remain.\\nTesting/logging: add an automated check that fails if a legacy-mapped flag is removed or undocumented.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.009218447Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T22:56:37.156889003Z","closed_at":"2026-02-27T22:56:37.156867743Z","close_reason":"FEATURE_PARITY.md now contains a comprehensive machine-checkable ledger mapping all 129 legacy bv flags to bvr implementation status (19 complete, 27 partial, 59 missing, 12 excluded, 2 bvr-only). Automated parity_ledger_documents_all_implemented_bvr_flags test verifies every implemented flag is documented. No unclassified surfaces remain.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cli","robot","spec"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-33w.1.1","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-05T00:07:49Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-33w.1.2","title":"Define TUI fidelity contract (layout breakpoints, keymaps, visual tokens)","description":"Background: visual parity requires explicit measurable criteria.\\nWork: capture reference behavior for width bands (~100/140/180), per-view component composition, keybinding semantics, modal flows, and textual/visual tokens (headers, lane cards, indicators).\\nAcceptance: contract doc includes objective pass/fail checks and fixture/screenshots references suitable for automated snapshot validation.\\nTesting/logging: define required snapshot IDs and keyflow scripts that later tasks must satisfy.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.086734633Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T23:01:57.304769088Z","closed_at":"2026-02-27T23:01:57.304743230Z","close_reason":"FEATURE_PARITY.md now contains comprehensive TUI Fidelity Contract with: layout structure (42/58 split, header/footer), 5 view mode specifications (Main/Board/Graph/Insights/History), complete keybinding matrix (pass/fail checkable per mode with 60+ bindings), visual token catalog (status/type icons, mini-bars, box drawing, section headers), 3 modal flow specifications (help/quit-confirm/search), and remaining fidelity gaps documented.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["spec","tui","ux"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-33w.1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-05T00:07:49Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-33w.1.3","title":"Freeze phased implementation and dependency gates from spec contract","description":"Background: parity closure needs sequencing discipline to avoid churn.\\nWork: convert contract into execution waves with explicit prerequisites, blocked-by rules, and completion criteria that tie directly to tests.\\nAcceptance: each downstream epic task links to concrete gates; no work item lacks verification strategy.\\nTesting/logging: add governance checklist to CI docs so unfinished gates are visible.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:56.166638253Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T23:12:43.450703583Z","closed_at":"2026-02-27T23:12:43.450685069Z","close_reason":"FEATURE_PARITY.md now contains a 4-wave phased implementation plan with explicit prerequisites, blocked-by rules, and concrete verification criteria (test names) for every gate. Wave 0 (spec contract) complete, Waves 1-4 mapped to 34 beads across 7 epics. Completion criteria defined: Waves 0-3 for functional equivalence, Wave 4 for release readiness.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["governance","planning","spec"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-33w.1.3","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-05T00:07:49Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-33w.1.3","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-05T00:07:49Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-33w.1.3","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-05T00:07:49Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
+{"id":"bd-33w.2","title":"Robot/CLI Surface Parity (Legacy 134 flags -> Rust complete coverage)","description":"Background: legacy bv exposes many robot and operational flags not yet in bvr.\\nGoal: close robot/CLI functional gap while preserving deterministic machine-readable contracts.\\nScope: missing robot commands, search/recipes/drift/schema/docs output surfaces, update/admin flags, and compatibility semantics.\\nAcceptance: all required legacy flags are either implemented with conformance evidence or explicitly excluded in spec with rationale.","status":"blocked","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-27T22:25:55.175200454Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-27T22:26:28.567071187Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cli","parity","robot"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-33w.2","depends_on_id":"bd-33w","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-05T00:07:49Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-33w.2","depends_on_id":"bd-33w.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-05T00:07:49Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
